			<div class="content" id="post-content-2371862">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Great page - author pages are the perfect places to talk about process and technical aspects of writing, so I'm very pleased to see another in that form.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yeah, I had a clever idea for something else, but I saw what you (and Decibelles, and WrongJohnSilver) had done and I realized useful is better than clever. So I copied you.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Seeing all your skips in a list, one thing that strikes me is the amount of variety - in subject matter, tone, format. That's rather impressive.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>To some extent, that's deliberate. I try to make sure that I am doing something differently whenever I can and I try to be aware of genre and style when I write.</p>
<p>I was thinking about this for the &quot;What's Your Specialty?&quot; thread, and I am not really able to answer that question.</p>

