															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251914" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;" >sirpudding</a></span> <span class="odate time_1441751089 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Sep 2015 22:24</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2372066">
									

<p>A neologism meaning a catastrophic break in reality replacing prior history with a new past. It's a portmanteau of &quot;ontological&quot; and &quot;cataclysm&quot;. Also called a &quot;reality quake&quot;. Coined, I believe, by Kenneth Hite.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Plainly, we have to face the possibility now that reality did fracture in or about the beginning of the year 1477. Equally plainly, it is possible that fragments of that prior history have existed in ours, becoming gradually less and less “real” as the universe moves on from the moment of fracture.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>–Mary Gentle, <em>Ash, A Secret History</em></p>
<p>In the scipverse, such a thing happened at the collapse of Daevite civilization, such that it completely erased them from existence. Also depending on how you think about it Islamic Samothrace may have been created or destroyed in a reality quake.</p>
<p>By the way, <em>Ash</em> is excellent (although trigger warning: has violence and sexual violence).</p>

							</div>

								
